## Verification Plan

### Automated (On CSF)

This is all verified post-training via the outputs the script already generates:

1. **Upload modified files to CSF:**
   ```powershell
   scp "D:/skin cancer project/train_fairface.py" m84149ji@csf3.itservices.manchester.ac.uk:~/skin-cancer/
   scp "D:/skin cancer project/submit_csf.sh" m84149ji@csf3.itservices.manchester.ac.uk:~/skin-cancer/
   ```

2. **Submit job:**
   ```bash
   cd ~/skin-cancer && sbatch submit_csf.sh
   ```

3. **Monitor:**
   ```bash
   squeue -u m84149ji
   tail -f logs/fairface_v2_<JOB_ID>.log
   ```

4. **Download results:**
   ```powershell
   scp -r m84149ji@csf3.itservices.manchester.ac.uk:~/skin-cancer/outputs/FairFace-Model-2.5/ "D:/skin cancer project/outputs/FairFace-Model-2.5/"
   ```

### Success Criteria

| Metric | v2.4 Baseline | v2.5 Target | Rationale |
|--------|:---:|:---:|-----------|
| **Type III Recall** | 3.8% | **≥15%** | Matching v2.2's breakthrough level |
| **Type II Recall** | 8.7% | **≥20%** | Matching v2.2's breakthrough level |
| Type VI Recall | 84.8% | **≥80%** | No significant regression |
| Type I Recall | 82.6% | **≥78%** | No significant regression |
| Macro F1 | 0.46 | **≥0.48** | Net improvement across all classes |
| Train/Val gap | Inverted (underfitting) | **Normal** (train ≥ val) | Training curves should look healthy |

### Manual Review

After downloading results, compare side-by-side:
- [fairface_confusion_matrix.png](file:///d:/skin%20cancer%20project/outputs/FairFace-Model-2.4/fairface_confusion_matrix.png) — Type IV column should shrink
- [fairface_training_curves.png](file:///d:/skin%20cancer%20project/outputs/FairFace-Model-2.4/fairface_training_curves.png) — Train acc should be ≥ val acc (no underfitting)
- [fairface_latent_space.png](file:///d:/skin%20cancer%20project/outputs/FairFace-Model-2.4/fairface_latent_space.png) — Middle types should show better separation
